        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks AG for his criticisms of CD’s views; finds it difficult to avoid using the term "natural selection" as an agent.</p> 
<p>Discusses crossing in <hi rend="italic">Fumaria</hi> and barnacles.</p> 
            <p>Has received a naturally crossed kidney bean in which the seed-coat has been affected by the pollen of the fertilising plant.</p>
            <p>Finds the rule of large genera having most varieties holds good and regards it as most important for his "principle of divergence".</p>
        </abstract>
